<p><strong>Singular and Plural Exercises with Answers (PDF)</strong></p>
<p><strong>Paragraph 1:</strong></p>
<p>Understanding the rules for forming singular and plural nouns is a foundational aspect of English grammar. This exercise provides a comprehensive guide, covering both regular and irregular nouns, to help you master this skill.</p>
<p><strong>Paragraph 2:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Regular Nouns:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>To form the plural of most nouns, add "-s" to the singular form.</li>
<li>Example: book -&gt; books, dog -&gt; dogs, leaf -&gt; leaves</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Irregular Nouns:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Some nouns have irregular plural forms that do not follow the "-s" rule.</li>
<li>Examples: foot -&gt; feet, child -&gt; children, mouse -&gt; mice</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Paragraph 3:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Singular or Plural? Choose the correct option:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<ol>
<li>The <strong>____</strong> is in the kitchen. (dog / dogs)</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>
<ol start="2">
<li>The <strong>____</strong> flew over the house. (bird / birds)</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>
<ol start="3">
<li>I have many <strong>____</strong>. (toy / toys)</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>
<ol start="4">
<li>The <strong>____</strong> is a pet. (cat / cats)</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>
<ol start="5">
<li>The <strong>____</strong> were delicious. (cookie / cookies)</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Paragraph 4:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with the correct plural form:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<ol>
<li>The children played with their <strong>____</strong>. (ball)</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>
<ol start="2">
<li>The farmer had a barn full of <strong>____</strong>. (cow)</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>
<ol start="3">
<li>We need to buy some <strong>____</strong> for the party. (balloon)</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>
<ol start="4">
<li>The teacher gave the students <strong>____</strong> to work on. (book)</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>
<ol start="5">
<li>I love to read <strong>____</strong>. (magazine)</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
